    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sanskrit word Prakriti or Prakruti has multiple meanings and is used in the Bhagavad Gita in different contexts. In the English language, we try to translate it to &amp;ldquo;Nature&amp;rdquo;. But, does this word really summarize the meaning of the Sanskrit word? To better understand, you need to look at these 25 slokas. You may not get a complete answer, but it will help you delve deeper and transcend existence.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
